=============================================================================
(I) Moved/Sorted Makefile.config to ``compile/'':
     (A) Makefile.config.gen.tun, Makefile.config.gen
     (B) Makefile.config.piny
     (C) Makefile.config.charm

(II) Placed charm++ routines in ``src_charm_driver/'' and
     created a directory structure:
     (A) compile                 : Makefile
     (B) load_balance            : map.C
     (C) orthog_ctrl             : ortho.C, Scalc.C
     (D) utility                 : util.C
     (E) e-density manipulations : cp_density_ctrl
     (F) e-state manipulations   : cp_state_ctrl
     (G) main                    : cpaimd.C, groups.C
     (H) mathlib                 : Blas fortran routines
     (I) sim_subroutines.C       : needs to be split

(III) PINY : Created  ``src_piny_physics/'' and copied some stuff from leanMD 
     (A) piny_to_driver : the interface of piny readonlys to charm_driver
     (B) interface      : routines to fill piny readonlys

(IV) Ab initio Phys : Divided qc_subroutines into PINY calculator classes
                       stored in ``src_piny_physics_v1.0/abinito_physics''
     (A) cp_integrate : Numerical integration.
     (B) cp_nonlocal  : Z-matrix stuff, kinetic energy.
     (C) cp_local     : Hartree, external. 
     (D) cp_orthog    : Orthogonalization.
     (E) cp_xc_fnctl  : Exchange correlation.

(IV) Classical Phys : Copied from LeanMD and created a directory tree
                      under ``src_piny_physics_v1.0/classical_physics''
     (A) top           : Physics_force_field.C
     (B) intra         : Intramolecular potential.
     (C) intra_con     : Constraint routines.
     (D) inter_real    : Intermolecular real space potential (Vdw+Coul)
     (E) inter_recip   : Intermolecular recip space potential (PME/Ewald)
     (F) vel_smpl_atms : Velocity sampling.

=============================================================================

